review_blob: Purchased at grocery store in Virginia, amazed only the 2nd rating since im across country. Hazy orange with thin head. Citrus aroma and taste, nice bitterness, medium bodied. Overall a delicious refreshing beer.Earlier Rating: 12/20/2007 Total Score: 3.2Considering the name its surprising that this beer is only moderately bitter. Other than that it isnt half bad, tastes pretty good but not what I expected. Aroma more fruity and malty than hops.
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Picked this up while on vacation in Orlando at Knightly Spirits. Maybe my expectations were too high being a big fan of Stones Sublimely  and Southern Tiers Iniquity black IPAs, but I expected more from this beer. Thought the hop profile was moderate at best.
beer_name: Terrapin Side Project Captn Krunkles Black IPA

review_blob: Cedar aged version of the regular Jai Alai IPA. I was lucky enough to get both beers in trade with Raiderfost and drink them back to back. It makes an already solid IPA even better and one of the more interesting, flavorful brews ive had in a while.
beer_name: Cigar City Humidor Series India Pale Ale

review_blob: Acquired in trade with Raiderfost. Really nice balanced IPA. Earthy, resiny hops with a touch of citrus give way to a nice malt backbone. Drank side by side with the Humidor series cedar aged Jai Alai which was so good it may have skewed my opinion on this one slightly.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: Hazy amber with a big thick head. Tart and yeasty in the front with a moderate hop aftertaste. Worth a try but not something id go out of my way to get again.
One of the best stouts ive ever had. Ive spent a lot more money on stouts that werent as good. If you factor in the price it may be along with Bells stouts the best bang for your buck.
nice citrus pine aroma, clear orange with a lot of floaters, a little sweetness in the front with piney bitter finish, medium bodied with good carbonation
Really nice beer, one of the better VA brewed beers. Got as part of a Dragon pack sampler, was impressed with every style but this s the highlight of the mix pack
Never disappointed in a Stone beer, This was not quite my favorite but ranks right up there. Cant wait to try it again after some cellaring, Then mabe it will be my fav.
One of my favorite IPAs ever, along with Dales pale ale, the IPA I most often return to

from Can, aroma faint, roasted malts. Thick black pour with small molasses colored head. 98 ibus barely noticeable with the heavy malt, more of a coffee bitterness than hops. Expected to like more than I did

This doesnt taste quite like a double IPA. But apparently it is. 9.2 alc and double hopped. Its well balanced which would usually be a good thing but when I go for an imperial IPA its because Im craving big time hops. But what the hell, how many imperials can you get for 2 bucks, not many. Good Value
Really nice american belgian ale. Easy drinking for a "big beer", lots of flavor with a fruity, malty and big spiciness. Some noticeable alcohol but big sweetness masks it well

What a great smoked porter! Full bodied, brown/black, smoky, roasty, malty. Would love to try this again with some ribs or bbq chicken. As good as it is the price is a little high. Even if it is better I dont know if its worth it when I can get 3 bottles of the Stone smoked for the same price. Nice bottle for the collection
beer_name: Left Hand SmokeJumper Imperial Smoked Porter

review_blob: Light amber color with a slight malty aroma. Great head and lacing with lots of carbonation, tons of large bubbles float rapidly to the surface giving it a nice mouthfeel. Flavor is well balanced with a spicy character. The end of the bottle can be a bit too yeasty.
Pretty bad, smells and tastes of corn, no wonder these beers are served with lime, anything to make it taste better
Light yellow thin body. Pretty typical mexican beer. watered down, not a lot of flavor.
This is a beer for hopheads only. very thin body, low malt presence. Basically just a lot of hops which is not necessarily a bad thing if you want a lighter beer without sacrificing a lot of flavor

Not the best witbier available. A little overboard with the herbs and spices. This smelled like a Bath and Body Works store. I wasnt sure if I should drink it or rub it on my skin. It wasnt horrible just odd. Definitely the worst of the sampler pack.
beer_name: Great Lakes Holy Moses White Ale

review_blob: From a Sampler pack, Really nice IPA but only my third favorite from a sampler pack of four. Love a good IPA but cant really say anything I havent said about 50 other IPAs already
beer_name: Great Lakes Burning River Pale Ale

review_blob: Brought by a friend from Cleveland. One of the better lager style beers available. If it was available to me I might just make it my summer session beer of choice.
From great lakes sampler pack, Really nice porter a little more hops than typical but still well balanced. Far and away the best beer in the sampler.

Thought this was a nice offering from Legend. Paired it with some gourmet fudge and have to say i enjoyed it. The guy who compared it to a bowl of cocoa pebbles is right on. Rich chocolate aroma and flavor with a bit of lactose sourness.

2006 Batch 22oz really good IPA. Not the prettiest beer pours a murky orange color, but thats about as far as you can go with any criticism. Nice citrus hoppy great tasting brew with a well hidden high alcohol content.
I remember enjoying this beer more in the past than I did this time. It pours about as beautifully as any beer can. Has a smooth creamy mouthfeel but is too flat. Not  whole lot in the way of flavor.

Pretty good american pilsener. A little hoppier than a pilsener should typically be, but not a bad thing. Very crisp and refreshing but has a grassy taste. Give one of these to your friend who only drinks miller lite for a special treat.

Dark red/brown color. Overpowering chinook hops. Some sweet maltiness tries to fight its way through but is ultimately overtaken with the hop bitterness. Decent beer overall, exactly what one would expect a sierra nevada barley wine to taste like

Did not particularly enjoy this one.Nice aroma of raspberries. flavor was tart and sour with no sweetness to balance it out. Big fan of CLipper Citys Heavy Seas collection, but could have done without this offering
beer_name: Clipper City Oxford Organic Raspberry Wheat

review_blob: Really nice Porter from Left Hand. Very roasty and chocolatey with out being too sweet. Rich malty flavor little hop presence. Cant wait to get my hands on a Smoke Jumper
Decent organic beer. Interesting a lager with so much hop presence I kind of liked the stark contrast between the sweetness of a lager with noticeable hop bitterness.
beer_name: Green Valley Brewing Wild Hop Lager

review_blob: Really nice ESB, copper pour, good lacing throughout. nice balanced aroma and flavor, crisp dry finish. ESBs not my favorite style, usually just a poor mans pale ale. But this one is somewhere in between.
not a very typical wheat beer, no sediment. Aroma and taste what youd expect sweet malts and lime. Not horrible at first taste but gets a little hard to finish.
beer_name: Blue Moon Rising Moon Spring Ale

review_blob: Sweet stouts never seem to get as much credit as other stout styles. Personally I love them. This was a very enjoyable beer and one i could drink all night. Everything youd expect from a nice stout maybe just  little lighter in body but not in flavor

Very nice IPA, pours with a great head and lacing throughout. intense pleasing aroma as good as any IPA out there. tastes great but not as unique the aroma, still on par with any non imperial IPA youll find

A nice stout, similar flavors to the kalamazoo and expedition but a little lighter bodied smoother and sweeter, not nearly as bold and complex as expedition but enjoyed it as much, or more, as the kalamazoo.
pours dark orange/brown with nice head. Sweet malty aroma, tastes like rock candy. obviously brown sugar but with notes of caramel and orange.
Run-of-the-mill stout, pretty plain for this style, not bad, has all of the characteristics of any good stout just not as pronounced
My least favorite Sierra Nevada, not very good at all, very boring, should be fed to livestock, tastes like chewing on straw
great IPA, nice citrusy and sweet aroma. Big hop flavor spicy and citrus, intense but still allows for some sweet fruity malts to make an appearance
nice euro lager, straw yellow, malty with slight hop nose, crisp refreshing session beer, dry finish
my favorite Abita brew. Nutty, roasty aroma and flavor. Nice bitter dry mouthfeel that you get from eating pecans present in the beer.
Nice APA, balanced malt and hop aroma. Amber color. Taste has a big spicy bitter bite on the tongue with a nice dry finish.
Probably my favorite american macro lager, too bad it was a special release. Miller should consider bringing this one back.

Pretty good brown ale, enjoyed everything about it except for an odd sour bite in the finish, get rid of that and its a nice brew. Had to try it while I could, apparently this one only comes around every 400 years
if I was allergic to gluten Id be glad someone made beer for me, but Im not and I will never drink this crap again. unpleasant sourness of rotten fruit
morimoto soba ale 22 oz. light to medium bodied, crisp and refreshing. a good session beer
A nice hoppy full-bodied brew, loads of grapefruit in the flavor as well as lemon and pine. pretty smooth and drinkable for such a "ruinous" concoction
Nice medium bodied porter. little aroma but tasty and smooth. nice malty mildly sweet flavor with less hops than expected from sierra nevada

moderate alc for an imperial stout makes it smoother than most. Pours like old strong coffee with a nice frothy big head. Nice combo of chocolate, coffee and roasted malts and oatmeal sweetness. Moderate hop presence
A great IPA nice head and lacing with a perfect goldenrod color. blend of citrus fruit (orange, grapefruit, lemon) and hops, nice effervesence and spicyness on the palate.
